SD-OD space

It can be useful to plot the score vs. orthogonal distances (SD and OD, respectively) to check that the training and test sets share the same space. This can be implemented by using function occsdod (one-class classification with SD and OD).

OCC model fitting 

model = occsdod()
fit!(model, fitm0, Xtrain)
fitm = model.fitm
@names fitm
@head dtrain = fitm.d

Final graph 

d = vcat(dtrain, dtest)
group = [repeat(["Train"], ntrain); repeat(["Test"], ntest)]
color = [(:red, .5), (:blue, .5)]
plotxy(d.d_sd, d.d_od, group; zeros = true, color, xlabel = "SD", ylabel = "OD").f
